cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.CR 

This paper deals with deep convolutional neural network models and their visualization techniques. Hence, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the bias in trained models, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper talks about the interpretation of deep CNN models, which can be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper mentions medical scan or imagery, which can be related to cs.CR (Computers and Society).
